SIMPLE: renowned
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Renowned
<hw>Re*nowned"</hw> <pr>(r?-nound")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Famous;
celebrated for great achievements, for distinguished qualities, or for
grandeur; eminent; <as>as, a <ex>renowned</ex> king</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Some <xex>renowned</xex> metropolis with glistering
spires.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These were the <qex>renowned</qex> of the congregation.</q>
<rj><qau>Num. i. 61.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Famous; famed; distinguished; noted; eminent;
celebrated; remarkable; wonderful. See <er>Famous</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renownedly</ent>⟦br⟧
